{"author":{"id":"ab495368f431cbc3ee3dfc99ecf12eeb8b429836cb37bed3d5a1646d08668d30"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1685388363,"nonce":"W3s91U4K2D24BOR8vGRAO2bPoY0=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5nL2cW","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5332","origin":"github"},"title":"plink: little bug with \"Chromosome(s)\" and \"Exclude Chromosome(s)\" options","message":"Options \"Chromosome(s)\" and \"Exclude Chromosome(s)\" do not allow to enter a hyphenated range or comma separated list. All hyphens and commas are converted to 'X' symbol, which leads to errors. For example, '1-22' is converted to '1X22'. The only variant to set several chromosomes is to separate them by whitespace like this: '1 2 3'.","files":null}]}